flowRoot.flowPara: The companies and politicians are destroying our planet.
But they are few in number,
and it is our compliance in the system that keeps them afloat.
Contact your local Earth Strike chapter!
Check earth-strike.com/map to find chapters in your area.
Join our protests and rallies throughout the year!
International events are scheduled for January 15, April 27, and August 1.
Talk to your friends and family, and scatter our pamphlets and stickers around your city.

The companies that contribute to climate change have little incentive to do otherwise. This is deeply unfortunate, but it is due to the demands of their stockholders and the influence that their wealth gives them over their regulators. Protests are great, but to the oil barons they matter less than their next million-dollar paycheque.

Our goal isn't to convince them that they should ignore their own personal incentives for the greater good. Our goal is to change these incentives, so that they have no choice but to do whats right, or risk losing their jobs and their livelihoods.

This is the purpose of a general strike. We force the hands of power by refusing to partake in the system propping them up. They hold most of the cards, but they cant take away the power we have to withhold our labour.
Our strike is a wake-up call to the upper class,
that they depend on us as much as we depend on them.
